[3
Date: Fri 12 Jan 2001 10:30:50 -0600
From: Barry Hartup <hartup@savingcranes.org>

Rabies in river otters has not gone unreported in the eastern United
States. Please see the article by Tom Serfass et al. which describes a
case from Pennsylvania associated with the Mid-Atlantic raccoon variant
rabies virus:
Serfass, T. et al. 1995. Rabies in a river otter (_Lutra canadensis_)
intended for reintroduction. Journal of Zoo and Wildlife Medicine 26(2):
311-314.
--
Barry K. Hartup, DVM, PhD
Director of Veterinary Services
International Crane Foundation
Box 447, E-11376 Shady Lane Road
Baraboo, WI 53913 USA
<hartup@savingcranes.org>
