[5
Date: Fri, 12 Jan 2001 21:34:01 -0200
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luiz_jacintho@uol.com.br>

A cautionary note should be added to this news report: rabies shots can be
relied as 100% effective only when a combination of passive (human rabies
immune globulin or equine rabies immune globulin) AND active immunization,
cell culture inactivated virus vaccine (a series of 5) is used, within a
relatively short interval after exposure. Even so, to be 100% effective,
part (as much as possible) of the immune globulin (HRIG or ERIG) must be
infiltrated around the wound.
Luiz Jacintho da Silva, M.D.
<ljsilva@promedmail.org>
